146
00:11:12,098 --> 00:11:13,258
Catch that boy!

147
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,171
They seem a little edgy.

148
00:11:22,209 --> 00:11:24,143
Our police become
very animated

149
00:11:24,177 --> 00:11:26,236
when it's an American
that's been kidnapped.

150
00:11:26,279 --> 00:11:28,406
You teach at the same
university as Anse Rainier.

151
00:11:28,448 --> 00:11:29,540
I do.

152
00:11:29,583 --> 00:11:31,175
Don't you think he's
worth looking for?

153
00:11:31,218 --> 00:11:33,209
By roughing up people who
had nothing to do with it?

154
00:11:33,253 --> 00:11:35,016
I've heard the group
taking responsibility

155
00:11:35,055 --> 00:11:36,113
recruits here.

156
00:11:36,156 --> 00:11:37,282
What makes you so sure

157
00:11:37,324 --> 00:11:38,518
they had nothing to do with it?

158
00:11:38,558 --> 00:11:40,651
They're my students.

159
00:11:40,694 --> 00:11:44,323
And they're innocent
until proven otherwise.

160
00:11:44,364 --> 00:11:46,298
I learned that from CSI: Miami.

161
00:11:46,333 --> 00:11:48,426
(laughs)

162
00:11:48,468 --> 00:11:49,560
Yeah.

163
00:11:49,603 --> 00:11:50,661
Hmm.

164
00:11:52,739 --> 00:11:56,437
Do you think he's still alive?

165
00:11:56,477 --> 00:11:59,469
(helicopter whirring)

166
00:12:05,219 --> 00:12:06,277
So tell me, Bobby,

167
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:08,015
