168
00:12:08,055 --> 00:12:09,955
Well, I'm still working on it,

169
00:12:09,991 --> 00:12:13,324
but so far the logline is,

170
00:12:13,361 --> 00:12:15,488
"Pakistan's New Militant Academia. "

171
00:12:15,530 --> 00:12:18,294
Am I part of the new
militant academia?

172
00:12:18,332 --> 00:12:19,799
I don't know.

173
00:12:19,834 --> 00:12:20,960
Are you?

174
00:12:24,739 --> 00:12:26,708
You know, the answer
to that question

175
00:12:26,742 --> 00:12:31,042
may challenge some of
your preconceived notions.

176
00:12:31,079 --> 00:12:32,376
Changez, I'm a journalist.

177
00:12:32,414 --> 00:12:34,882
Generally, we try to avoid
preconceived notions.

178
00:12:34,917 --> 00:12:36,043
But of course.

179
00:12:36,084 --> 00:12:37,381
- You mind if I...
- Yes.

180
00:12:37,419 --> 00:12:39,387
I only ask one thing.

181
00:12:39,421 --> 00:12:41,889
That you please listen
to the whole story

182
00:12:41,924 --> 00:12:42,913
from the very beginning,

183
00:12:42,958 --> 00:12:44,755
not just bits and pieces.

184
00:12:45,994 --> 00:12:47,325
Do I have your word?

185
00:12:47,362 --> 00:12:48,420
You do.

186
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:53,125
(electronic beep)

187
00:12:53,168 --> 00:12:55,068
Looks can be deceiving.

188
00:12:57,407 --> 00:12:59,170
I am a lover of America.

189
00:13:01,044 --> 00:13:03,478
Although I was raised to feel
very Pakistani.

190
00:13:05,381 --> 00:13:08,373
After all, the blood of princes
runs in my veins.

191
00:13:09,652 --> 00:13:11,051
Perhaps that's an exaggeration.

192
00:13:11,087 --> 00:13:14,352
Let's say the princes and I
moved in the same circles.

193
00:13:15,758 --> 00:13:17,589
We attended the same schools...

194
00:13:18,795 --> 00:13:21,127
Lived in the same neighborhoods.

195
00:13:21,164 --> 00:13:22,153
(grunts)

196
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:26,299
But all of a sudden,
there were new princes in town.

197
00:13:26,336 --> 00:13:27,598
(engine grinding)

198
00:13:27,637 --> 00:13:28,626
Hey, Chingu!

199
00:13:28,671 --> 00:13:29,639
(engine turns over)

200
00:13:29,673 --> 00:13:31,641
Buy a new car.

201
00:13:31,675 --> 00:13:33,472
Time to junk your oxcart.

202
00:13:33,510 --> 00:13:34,704
(laughter)

203
00:13:34,745 --> 00:13:36,235
(in English)
Yes, we still had the prestige

204
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:38,009
