(in Urdu) What vulgar clothes.

220
00:14:11,616 --> 00:14:14,847
No one will marry you.

221
00:14:14,886 --> 00:14:16,183
Ammi, please.

222
00:14:16,221 --> 00:14:17,848
I'm the Bond girl.

223
00:14:17,889 --> 00:14:19,356
It's no joke.

224
00:14:19,391 --> 00:14:21,450
They're lining up.

225
00:14:21,493 --> 00:14:24,053
Go, work in India.

226
00:14:24,095 --> 00:14:25,426
There, anything goes.

227
00:14:25,463 --> 00:14:27,158
(laughter)

228
00:14:27,198 --> 00:14:28,665
"Though memories fade,

229
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:31,601
"may Allah never free you

230
00:14:31,636 --> 00:14:36,097
from my love. "

231
00:14:36,142 --> 00:14:37,973
(grumbling)

232
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:41,446
Changez, remember,
your father's a poet.

233
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,674
Sing for us.

234
00:14:42,715 --> 00:14:43,704
Mm-mm.

235
00:14:43,749 --> 00:14:45,944
He doesn't want to sing
those songs anymore, Ajju.

236
00:14:45,985 --> 00:14:47,976
He's an American now.

237
00:14:48,020 --> 00:14:49,749
Va, va, va, va...

238
00:14:49,789 --> 00:14:51,086
(speaking Urdu)

239
00:14:51,123 --> 00:14:52,556
Listen, son.

240
00:14:58,431 --> 00:15:00,456
He fusses over you
because he loves you.

241
00:15:00,499 --> 00:15:02,763
You know that, right?

242
00:15:02,802 --> 00:15:03,894
Cigarette?

243
00:15:05,038 --> 00:15:06,665
Poems don't buy generators.

244
00:15:06,707 --> 00:15:08,265
Somebody has to be
where the money is.

245
00:15:08,308 --> 00:15:11,869
Hey, Chingu,
take me to New York with you.

246
00:15:11,912 --> 00:15:14,244
I could be the dazzling
new ethnic friend

247
00:15:14,281 --> 00:15:16,044
