271
00:16:37,132 --> 00:16:39,032
And I'm about to graduate
summa cum laude.

272
00:16:39,068 --> 00:16:40,900
Good... although I've heard
that line several times today.

273
00:16:40,937 --> 00:16:42,529
What else?

274
00:16:42,572 --> 00:16:44,802
Well, I also played
varsity soccer

275
00:16:44,841 --> 00:16:45,933
four years straight.

276
00:16:45,975 --> 00:16:48,205
I'm glad you got some exercise.

277
00:16:48,244 --> 00:16:51,304
Changes, a position at our firm
as a financial analyst

278
00:16:51,347 --> 00:16:54,339
is one the most sought-after
jobs in the entire world.

279
00:16:54,384 --> 00:16:56,011
Lift up the hood.

280
00:16:56,052 --> 00:16:58,543
Show me what makes you run.

281
00:16:58,588 --> 00:16:59,782
Where are you from?

282
00:16:59,823 --> 00:17:01,814
Lahore in Pakistan.

283
00:17:04,994 --> 00:17:06,256
Are you on financial aid?

284
00:17:07,597 --> 00:17:08,757
Yes, I am.

285
00:17:08,798 --> 00:17:10,595
It's more difficult for
an international student

286
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:12,261
to be accepted at an
Ivy League school

287
00:17:12,303 --> 00:17:14,100
if they apply for aid.

288
00:17:14,138 --> 00:17:15,730
