in the last week.

1091
00:56:45,548 --> 00:56:46,845
Is this the line for chai?

1092
00:56:46,882 --> 00:56:48,577
You hear about Sodhi
in Arizona?

1093
00:56:48,617 --> 00:56:50,552
They shot him
right on the street.

1094
00:56:50,587 --> 00:56:51,815
It's really bad for the Sikhs.

1095
00:56:51,855 --> 00:56:53,948
Sikhs are in trouble.

1096
00:56:53,990 --> 00:56:55,981
Any beard or turban is a target.

1097
00:56:57,093 --> 00:56:58,993
Not a problem for you, eh?

1098
00:56:59,029 --> 00:57:02,726
Suited, booted.
Good for you.

1099
00:57:02,766 --> 00:57:03,755
(speaks Urdu)

1100
00:57:03,800 --> 00:57:04,789
No plastic here.

1101
00:57:07,871 --> 00:57:09,862
- Give him his tea.
- No, no, please.

1102
00:57:09,906 --> 00:57:11,430
Don't embarrass me.

1103
00:57:11,474 --> 00:57:13,908
You are like my brother.

1104
00:57:13,944 --> 00:57:15,002
Thanks.

1105
00:57:17,080 --> 00:57:18,945
I might have been suited
and booted,

1106
00:57:18,982 --> 00:57:21,645
but I felt just as vulnerable
as they did.

1107
00:57:22,920 --> 00:57:24,979
There was only one place
I felt safe...

1108
00:57:26,324 --> 00:57:27,621
With her.

1109
00:57:27,658 --> 00:57:29,216
You want to learn
how to say "love"?

1110
00:57:29,260 --> 00:57:30,727
Yeah.

1111
00:57:30,761 --> 00:57:32,558
There's not just one way
of saying it.

1112
00:57:32,597 --> 00:57:34,827
- There's, like, two or three.
- Okay, okay.

1113
00:57:37,535 --> 00:57:39,730
Okay, so there's ishq.

1114
00:57:39,770 --> 00:57:40,786
Ishq.

1115
00:57:41,391 --> 00:57:42,335
Ishq.

1116
00:57:42,373 --> 00:57:44,238
(chuckles)

1117
00:57:44,275 --> 00:57:45,242
Ishq.

1118
00:57:45,276 --> 00:57:46,903
Mm.
Well done.

1119
00:57:46,944 --> 00:57:49,913
And then there's pyaar.

1120
00:57:49,947 --> 00:57:52,280
Pyaar.

1121
00:57:52,317 --> 00:57:53,375
That's quite good.

1122
00:57:53,418 --> 00:57:54,407
Yeah?
(laughs)

1123
00:57:54,453 --> 00:57:56,580
- You're good at this.
- Pyaar.

1124
00:57:56,622 --> 00:57:58,487
You said this word before
to someone?

1125
00:57:58,523 --> 00:57:59,888
Ishq.
Pyaar.

1126
00:57:59,925 --> 00:58:02,223
This isn't your first time, is it?

1127
00:58:02,260 --> 00:58:05,787
(laughing)

1128
00:58:05,831 --> 00:58:08,823
(laughter)

1129
00:58:08,867 --> 00:58:11,836
(meandering guitar music)

1130
00:58:11,870 --> 00:58:17,355
♪

1131
00:58:34,427 --> 00:58:36,068
Mohabbat.

1132
00:58:36,980 --> 00:58:38,222
Mohabbat.

1133
00:58:38,257 --> 00:58:39,195
(chuckles)

1134
00:58:42,001 --> 00:58:43,866
I can't believe
they're not there.

1135
00:58:47,707 --> 00:58:53,337
♪

1136
00:59:15,836 --> 00:59:16,996
It's crazy.

1137
00:59:18,372 --> 00:59:20,670
It was a time of uncertainty.

1138
00:59:20,708 --> 00:59:23,871
For me, the only things certain
were love and profit.

1139
00:59:25,379 --> 00:59:27,575
It wasn't long before the
economic laws of nature

1140
00:59:27,615 --> 00:59:29,583
reasserted themselves.

1141
00:59:29,617 --> 00:59:32,916
Small companies were again
swallowed up by big ones.

1142
00:59:32,954 --> 00:59:35,218
Those that didn't grow would die.

1143
00:59:36,758 --> 00:59:38,919
Some stakeholders are obviously
you people right here.

1144
00:59:38,960 --> 00:59:40,154
That's why need to revisit...

1145
00:59:40,195 --> 00:59:41,890
For the 25 years that
I've worked here,

1146
00:59:41,930 --> 00:59:43,557
per union rules,

1147
00:59:43,598 --> 00:59:45,293
we only take those requests
in writing.

1148
00:59:45,333 --> 00:59:46,459
See, with due respect,

1149
00:59:46,501 --> 00:59:48,765
that is exactly the kind
of bureaucratic mind-set

1150
00:59:48,803 --> 00:59:50,031
we're trying to challenge here.

1151
00:59:50,071 --> 00:59:51,698
I am not a bureaucrat.

1152
00:59:51,740 --> 00:59:53,105
We don't have to like each other.

1153
00:59:53,141 --> 00:59:54,870
We just have to get the job done.

1154
00:59:54,909 --> 00:59:56,308
Now, pull out the union contracts.

1155
00:59:56,344 --> 00:59:57,834
We might need to cancel
some of them.

1156
00:59:59,882 --> 01:00:01,543
- He's young.
- I've worked here 25 years.

1157
01:00:01,584 --> 01:00:03,415
What the hell am I supposed to do?

1158
01:00:03,452 --> 01:00:05,113
(indistinct conversations)

1159
01:00:27,343 --> 01:00:28,537
Hi, stranger.

1160
01:00:28,577 --> 01:00:30,010
When are you coming back?

1161
01:00:30,045 --> 01:00:31,206
I miss you.

1162
01:01:11,489 --> 01:01:14,583
Fuck you, Osama.

1163
01:01:14,625 --> 01:01:15,785
(spits)

1164
01:01:25,436 --> 01:01:26,903
A tiny slice of violence

1165
01:01:26,938 --> 01:01:28,929
had wormed its way into my life,

1166
01:01:28,973 --> 01:01:31,066
and I didn't know
how to remove it.

1167
01:01:38,383 --> 01:01:41,511
What was soft inside me
fell away.

1168
01:01:41,553 --> 01:01:44,215
What was hard became harder.

1169
01:01:47,693 --> 01:01:50,685
(electronic beeping)

1170
01:01:52,631 --> 01:01:54,565
Talk to me, Bobby.
What's going on?

1171
01:01:54,600 --> 01:01:56,033
I need more time.

1172
01:01:56,068 --> 01:01:59,595
You're exposed, and the clock
is ticking on Rainier.

1173
01:01:59,638 --> 01:02:00,798
Turn your target now,

1174
01:02:00,839 --> 01:02:02,033
or we're taking him to Peshawar

1175
01:02:02,074 --> 01:02:03,541
to put the screws on him.

1176
01:02:03,575 --> 01:02:04,633
Okay.

1177
01:02:09,816 --> 01:02:11,613
What did Massoud do
to members of his force

1178
01:02:11,651 --> 01:02:13,516
that collaborated
with the Taliban?

1179
01:02:15,054 --> 01:02:16,214
He slit their throats.

1180
01:02:16,256 --> 01:02:17,416
Yes, he did.

1181
01:02:18,992 --> 01:02:21,358
Do you want that
to happen to me, Bobby?

1182
01:02:21,394 --> 01:02:23,589
Is there something
you're not telling me?

1183
01:02:23,630 --> 01:02:25,291
Juniad, look at that.

1184
01:02:26,833 --> 01:02:27,857
Careful.

1185
01:02:27,901 --> 01:02:28,959
Watch out.

1186
01:02:29,969 --> 01:02:31,869
Brother...

1187
01:02:31,905 --> 01:02:34,271
Khan, sir, let's go down.

1188
01:02:37,176 --> 01:02:38,337
Hurry.

1189
01:02:40,247 --> 01:02:42,215
Each moment is precious,
Bobby.

1190
01:02:42,249 --> 01:02:44,308
Come.
It's time to go inside.

1191
01:02:44,351 --> 01:02:47,047
Where is the security guard?

1192
01:02:59,133 --> 01:03:01,101
Hello?

1193
01:03:01,135 --> 01:03:02,864
I'm talking to you, Ma.
Hello?

1194
01:03:02,903 --> 01:03:04,393
(speaking Urdu)

1195
01:03:04,438 --> 01:03:05,996
Keep the candles safely.

1196
01:03:06,040 --> 01:03:09,168
Trouble could break out anytime.

1197
01:03:09,209 --> 01:03:12,907
The sweets go in the kitchen,
the soft drinks too.

1198
01:03:12,948 --> 01:03:15,246
Ma, you're being stubborn.

1199
01:03:15,283 --> 01:03:17,308
I'll make one phone call
to the caterers.

1200
01:03:17,352 --> 01:03:19,183
They will handle everything, okay?

1201
01:03:19,220 --> 01:03:21,814
Baita, with the shortages,
the prices have doubled up.

1202
01:03:21,856 --> 01:03:23,187
We just can't afford it.

1203
01:03:23,224 --> 01:03:25,192
No, what we can't afford
is for you to collapse,

1204
01:03:25,226 --> 01:03:26,784
okay, because you're trying
to organize

1205
01:03:26,828 --> 01:03:28,523
your daughter's wedding
singlehandedly.

1206
01:03:28,563 --> 01:03:30,861
Just let me do it.
It's done.

1207
01:03:30,899 --> 01:03:32,059
(sighs)

1208
01:03:33,835 --> 01:03:35,132
My prince.

1209
01:03:35,170 --> 01:03:37,798
Out of my sight.

1210
01:03:37,839 --> 01:03:39,397
One thing.

1211
01:03:39,441 --> 01:03:40,499
Don't tell Abu.

1212
01:03:40,542 --> 01:03:42,272
Okay, I won't.

1213
01:03:42,311 --> 01:03:44,472
Okay, talk later.

1214
01:03:44,513 --> 01:03:45,480
Love you, baita.

1215
01:03:45,514 --> 01:03:46,503
Uh-huh.
Okay.

1216
01:03:46,549 --> 01:03:47,538
God be with you.

1217
01:03:47,583 --> 01:03:48,641
(camera shutter clicks)

1218
01:03:48,684 --> 01:03:50,174
Hello!
Enough already!

1219
01:03:50,219 --> 01:03:51,550
- Just... just look at me.
- Hello?

1220
01:03:51,587 --> 01:03:53,452
Just look at... okay, fine.
Fine, fine, fine.

1221
01:03:53,489 --> 01:03:54,820
You're unbelievable.
Do you know that?

1222
01:03:54,857 --> 01:03:56,017
I'm worried about my mom here.

1223
01:03:56,058 --> 01:03:58,185
She's going nuts
because of the wedding.

1224
01:03:58,227 --> 01:04:00,422
A wedding gets her closer
to grandchildren.

1225
01:04:00,463 --> 01:04:02,897
That's what she wants, right?

1226
01:04:02,932 --> 01:04:04,092
Yeah, I guess.

1227
01:04:06,969 --> 01:04:09,437
I made your mom and dad
something for the wedding.

1228
01:04:12,676 --> 01:04:14,701
(laughs)

1229
01:04:14,745 --> 01:04:16,144
That's why you wanted the photos?

1230
01:04:16,179 --> 01:04:18,374
Your ma is so gorgeous.

1231
01:04:18,415 --> 01:04:20,815
Mm.

1232
01:04:20,851 --> 01:04:22,182
You're gorgeous.
Thank you.

1233
01:04:22,219 --> 01:04:23,243
Mm.

1234
01:04:31,161 --> 01:04:32,651
Do you ever think about kids?

1235
01:04:35,899 --> 01:04:37,423
Um...

1236
01:04:39,469 --> 01:04:40,595
I did before,

1237
01:04:40,637 --> 01:04:42,229
but the world's a little scarier now,

1238
01:04:42,272 --> 01:04:44,172
so I'm not as sure
as I used to be.

1239
01:04:48,613 --> 01:04:50,046
My parents never said it
out loud,

1240
01:04:50,081 --> 01:04:51,605
but I know they want
two things in life.

1241
01:04:51,649 --> 01:04:54,641
They want security
in their old age,

1242
01:04:54,685 --> 01:04:56,983
and they want grandchildren.

1243
01:04:57,021 --> 01:04:59,717
And you want to
give that to them.

1244
01:04:59,757 --> 01:05:01,418
Yeah.
They're my parents.

1245
01:05:02,460 --> 01:05:04,155
You have a sense of filial duty.

1246
01:05:06,531 --> 01:05:08,362
Yeah, I guess
I'm old-fashioned like that.

1247
01:05:10,368 --> 01:05:11,460
It's nice.

1248
01:05:13,604 --> 01:05:15,504
So does that mean
you're persuadable?

1249
01:05:20,712 --> 01:05:21,804
I don't know.

1250
01:05:31,957 --> 01:05:32,946
(sighs)

1251
01:05:47,172 --> 01:05:48,663
(yawns)

1252
01:05:48,708 --> 01:05:49,868
(sobs)

1253
01:05:59,285 --> 01:06:00,877
Hey.

1254
01:06:00,920 --> 01:06:02,046
(sniffles)

1255
01:06:02,088 --> 01:06:04,522
Erica?

1256
01:06:04,557 --> 01:06:05,649
Hey, what is it?

1257
01:06:05,692 --> 01:06:06,784
What's wrong?

1258
01:06:11,030 --> 01:06:12,122
Erica...

1259
01:06:13,299 --> 01:06:14,459
Ah.

1260
01:06:17,003 --> 01:06:18,994
I can't believe I'm talking
about having kids

1261
01:06:19,038 --> 01:06:20,301
with another man.

1262
01:06:24,111 --> 01:06:25,408
Honey, it was just talking.

1263
01:06:25,446 --> 01:06:26,640
It was just fooling around.

1264
01:06:26,680 --> 01:06:28,238
And I'm not another man.

1265
01:06:28,282 --> 01:06:29,579
No, no, no.
No, no.

1266
01:06:29,617 --> 01:06:31,778
You are another man.

1267
01:06:33,954 --> 01:06:34,943
(sobs)

1268
01:06:34,989 --> 01:06:36,149
You are.

1269
01:06:40,661 --> 01:06:43,653
(crying)

1270
01:06:48,135 --> 01:06:51,572
Chris... he didn't have any family.

1271
01:06:51,606 --> 01:06:55,064
Not like you.
I was his family, okay?

1272
01:06:55,110 --> 01:06:58,273
I was his family,
and I'm forgetting him.

1273
01:07:01,850 --> 01:07:03,408
Oh, God.

1274
01:07:03,451 --> 01:07:06,318
You know, I had been...
I'd been drinking,

1275
01:07:06,354 --> 01:07:09,323
and Chris asked me
if I was okay to drive,

1276
01:07:09,357 --> 01:07:10,984
and I said yes.

1277
01:07:14,396 --> 01:07:15,556
I killed him.

1278
01:07:20,936 --> 01:07:21,925
(sighs)
Oh, God.

1279
01:07:21,970 --> 01:07:23,939
Sometimes I just wish

1280
01:07:23,973 --> 01:07:26,464
I could take a break
from being myself.

1281
01:07:31,747 --> 01:07:32,873
(sniffles)

1282
01:07:38,354 --> 01:07:39,514
Me too.

1283
01:07:41,390 --> 01:07:44,018
Following the Parliament
attack in New Delhi,

1284
01:07:44,060 --> 01:07:47,086
the troops are gathering
at the border.

1285
01:07:47,129 --> 01:07:52,226
The fear of war between
India and Pakistan...

1286
01:07:52,268 --> 01:07:54,897
Nuclear powers,
grows every day.

1287
01:07:54,938 --> 01:07:56,337
(sighs)

1288
01:07:56,373 --> 01:07:58,898
How many weddings have
a bomb shelter contingency plan?

1289
01:07:58,942 --> 01:08:00,910
The world couldn't wait
one more week

1290
01:08:00,944 --> 01:08:02,172
before exploding itself?

1291
01:08:02,212 --> 01:08:04,043
Hello. Let's stick to
happier subjects.

1292
01:08:04,081 --> 01:08:05,810
How's the groom?

1293
01:08:05,849 --> 01:08:07,248
He's an actor, so...

1294
01:08:07,284 --> 01:08:09,980
A working actor
but an actor nonetheless.

1295
01:08:10,020 --> 01:08:12,955
Poor Abu keeps his
heart medication close at hand.

1296
01:08:12,990 --> 01:08:14,617
You know, if the war
doesn't kill him...

1297
01:08:14,658 --> 01:08:15,818
The wedding costs will.

1298
01:08:15,859 --> 01:08:18,259
(speaking Urdu)

1299
01:08:18,295 --> 01:08:19,455
Move on.

1300
01:08:22,266 --> 01:08:24,359
They never stop girls.

1301
01:08:24,401 --> 01:08:25,561
(both laugh)

1302
01:08:27,505 --> 01:08:29,939
Pakistan was born into
violence 50 years ago.

1303
01:08:29,974 --> 01:08:32,943
We knew how to cope.

1304
01:08:32,977 --> 01:08:34,205
As the tensions became worse,

1305
01:08:34,245 --> 01:08:36,611
the biryanis became
more delicious,

1306
01:08:36,648 --> 01:08:38,445
the bootleggers
more frequent,

1307
01:08:38,483 --> 01:08:41,247
and the celebrations
more raucous.

1308
01:08:41,286 --> 01:08:44,255
(singing in Urdu)

1309
01:08:44,289 --> 01:08:49,545
♪

1310
01:09:03,108 --> 01:09:05,440
Here comes the groom!

1311
01:09:12,184 --> 01:09:13,617
Really?

1312
01:09:13,652 --> 01:09:16,815
Girls, be on time to dress her
for the wedding tomorrow, huh?

1313
01:09:16,855 --> 01:09:19,790
(laughter)

1314
01:09:19,825 --> 01:09:21,759
Did you make this?

1315
01:09:21,794 --> 01:09:22,920
Show me your ring.

1316
01:09:24,263 --> 01:09:26,026
(laughing)

1317
01:09:26,065 --> 01:09:30,059
(indistinct conversation)

1318
01:09:30,103 --> 01:09:32,731
What are you thinking about?

1319
01:09:32,772 --> 01:09:35,172
Just how much you must love
all this attention, no?

1320
01:09:36,276 --> 01:09:37,334
Not about your girlfriend?

1321
01:09:37,377 --> 01:09:38,401
(laughs)

1322
01:09:42,048 --> 01:09:45,017
(man singing melancholy tune in Urdu)

1323
01:09:45,051 --> 01:09:47,645
♪

1324
01:09:47,687 --> 01:09:50,679
(speaking Urdu)

1325
01:09:54,127 --> 01:09:56,618
Your turn next, Nasreen, hmm?

1326
01:09:58,198 --> 01:09:59,688
Find me a guy now.

1327
01:10:01,569 --> 01:10:04,538
Lovely girl, and from a good family.

1328
01:10:05,806 --> 01:10:08,798
But you can't consider her

1329
01:10:08,843 --> 01:10:11,141
because you're an ocean away.

1330
01:10:11,178 --> 01:10:13,408
Luckily, Abu, they have women
in New York too, you know.

1331
01:10:13,447 --> 01:10:15,415
(chuckles)
I'm sure they do.

1332
01:10:19,820 --> 01:10:22,448
What exactly do you do
at the Underwood?

1333
01:10:22,490 --> 01:10:23,821
It's Underwood Samson.

1334
01:10:25,960 --> 01:10:28,224
We help companies to figure out
how much they're worth,

1335
01:10:28,262 --> 01:10:29,490
and then we make suggestions

1336
01:10:29,530 --> 01:10:31,395
so that they can increase their value.

1337
01:10:31,432 --> 01:10:33,162
Hmm.

1338
01:10:33,201 --> 01:10:34,361
So...

1339
01:10:36,405 --> 01:10:38,430
I'm a fruit seller.

1340
01:10:38,473 --> 01:10:40,270
You don't buy my guavas.

1341
01:10:40,308 --> 01:10:42,367
- You don't sell me guavas.
- No.

1342
01:10:42,411 --> 01:10:44,470
I pay you to tell me,

1343
01:10:44,513 --> 01:10:48,415
"The price of the guava
is 8 rupees. "

1344
01:10:48,450 --> 01:10:50,884
Yes, but I can also help you
to increase the value

1345
01:10:50,919 --> 01:10:52,318
of your whole fruit stand.

1346
01:10:52,354 --> 01:10:54,015
With redundancies.

1347
01:10:55,490 --> 01:10:58,459
So two fruit sellers become one,

1348
01:10:58,493 --> 01:11:00,290
and the money is saved.

1349
01:11:00,328 --> 01:11:01,761
Terrific.

1350
01:11:01,797 --> 01:11:02,821
I don't see the point.

1351
01:11:02,864 --> 01:11:04,297
(ceramic shatters)

1352
01:11:04,332 --> 01:11:05,766
I'll send you back
to your village!

1353
01:11:05,802 --> 01:11:06,791
Sorry, sir.

1354
01:11:11,174 --> 01:11:13,574
In the tent, the supervisor
will fire him.

1355
01:11:13,609 --> 01:11:16,237
That young man
drops one plate,

1356
01:11:16,279 --> 01:11:18,873
and his livelihood is gone.

1357
01:11:18,915 --> 01:11:20,246
I should talk to the supervisor.

1358
01:11:20,283 --> 01:11:22,513
No, no, no, no, no.

1359
01:11:22,552 --> 01:11:23,917
Come here.

1360
01:11:23,953 --> 01:11:26,513
Your empathy is aroused

1361
01:11:26,556 --> 01:11:29,855
because of this one man
whose face you can see.

1362
01:11:29,892 --> 01:11:31,860
But with one line
of your pen,

1363
01:11:31,894 --> 01:11:33,657
thousands of people
lose their livelihoods.

1364
01:11:33,696 --> 01:11:34,685
Abu, you know what?

1365
01:11:34,730 --> 01:11:35,719
A lot of people...

1366
01:11:35,765 --> 01:11:37,131
middle-class people,
shareholders...

1367
01:11:37,167 --> 01:11:38,657
they all benefit
from what I do.

1368
01:11:40,437 --> 01:11:42,371
You tell yourself
what you want to.

1369
01:11:44,141 --> 01:11:47,133
(humming)

1370
01:11:48,312 --> 01:11:51,941
(indistinct conversation)

1371
01:11:51,982 --> 01:11:53,677
You see your mother's handiwork?

1372
01:11:55,786 --> 01:11:59,153
If I told you the amount
your Ammi had to work with,

1373
01:11:59,189 --> 01:12:00,315
you wouldn't believe me.

1374
01:12:00,357 --> 01:12:01,824
(scoffs)

1375
01:12:01,859 --> 01:12:02,951
What is it?

1376
01:12:02,993 --> 01:12:04,187
- Nothing.
- What, nothing?

1377
01:12:04,228 --> 01:12:05,820
Nothing?

1378
01:12:05,863 --> 01:12:08,195
Never choke on a true word, son.

1379
01:12:09,601 --> 01:12:12,126
Well, she had some assistance.

1380
01:12:12,170 --> 01:12:13,228
What do you mean?

1381
01:12:13,271 --> 01:12:14,397
I mean that this job of mine

1382
01:12:14,439 --> 01:12:15,770
that you don't see the point of

1383
01:12:15,807 --> 01:12:18,298
actually helped to create
this celebration, all right?

1384
01:12:19,844 --> 01:12:20,868
- Excuse me.
- No, no, Abu.

1385
01:12:20,912 --> 01:12:22,038
I'm just trying to tell you

1386
01:12:22,080 --> 01:12:25,481
that this work of mine
can be useful to us.

1387
01:12:25,517 --> 01:12:27,280
(man singing in Urdu)

1388
01:12:27,318 --> 01:12:29,616
You've made your point very well.

1389
01:12:29,654 --> 01:12:33,215
Thank you.

1390
01:12:33,258 --> 01:12:37,217
♪ You say things
to burn the heart... ♪

1391
01:12:37,262 --> 01:12:39,162
♪

1392
01:12:39,197 --> 01:12:42,190
(speaking indistinctly)

1393
01:12:42,234 --> 01:12:46,193
♪ You speak of a nest
now broken... ♪

1394
01:12:46,238 --> 01:12:51,505
♪

1395
01:12:51,544 --> 01:12:55,503
♪ You inflict such suffering... ♪

1396
01:12:55,548 --> 01:13:00,247
♪

1397
01:13:00,286 --> 01:13:04,245
♪ Yet say I must smile... ♪

1398
01:13:04,290 --> 01:13:10,099
♪

1399
01:13:20,040 --> 01:13:22,941
My wisest ally, and I'd cut
him to the quick.

1400
01:13:22,976 --> 01:13:25,206
Only his pride.

1401
01:13:25,245 --> 01:13:27,543
Please, Changez,
don't let yours get in the way

1402
01:13:27,581 --> 01:13:28,775
of doing the right thing.

1403
01:13:28,815 --> 01:13:29,907
What would you have me do?

1404
01:13:29,950 --> 01:13:31,850
Help us find Rainier.

1405
01:13:31,885 --> 01:13:32,943
(electronic beeping)

1406
01:13:32,986 --> 01:13:35,113
Changez...

1407
01:13:35,155 --> 01:13:36,315
Work with us.

1408
01:13:38,758 --> 01:13:40,191
The agency has discretionary funds

1409
01:13:40,226 --> 01:13:41,386
for this kind of thing.

1410
01:13:41,428 --> 01:13:43,363
We can protect your family,
relocate them.

1411
01:13:46,000 --> 01:13:47,991
Bobby, you promised
to listen to me, didn't you?

1412
01:13:49,704 --> 01:13:52,036
Did you not hear
a word I just said?

1413
01:13:52,073 --> 01:13:54,837
There are some things
that money cannot fix.

1414
01:13:56,577 --> 01:13:58,374
When I returned
to America,

1415
01:13:58,412 --> 01:14:00,141
I found that the life
I was building

1416
01:14:00,181 --> 01:14:01,910
had begun to slip out of reach.

1417
01:14:01,949 --> 01:14:04,918
(melancholy guitar music)

1418
01:14:04,952 --> 01:14:09,082
♪

1419
01:14:09,123 --> 01:14:10,590
Should get this guy a razor.

1420
01:14:10,625 --> 01:14:12,058
Yeah, hi, Erica, it's me.

1421
01:14:12,093 --> 01:14:13,390
Can you pick up, please?

1422
01:14:13,427 --> 01:14:15,658
I haven't heard from you
in a few days now.

1423
01:14:15,697 --> 01:14:18,996
And I don't know what kind of
magical artistic masterpieces

1424
01:14:19,034 --> 01:14:21,832
you're cooking up,
but I miss you.

1425
01:14:21,870 --> 01:14:23,462
Hi.
Hi, sweetie.

1426
01:14:23,505 --> 01:14:26,736
Ah, that is the sound
I wanted to hear!

1427
01:14:26,775 --> 01:14:28,072
Okay, listen.
Hear me out.

1428
01:14:28,110 --> 01:14:29,270
I know you're on a deadline.

1429
01:14:29,311 --> 01:14:30,972
My show's in three days.

1430
01:14:31,013 --> 01:14:34,005
Look, I'm so under
the gun right now.

1431
01:14:34,049 --> 01:14:36,108
I just... I can't talk.

1432
01:14:36,151 --> 01:14:37,413
- Okay, but dinner.
Just dinner.

1433
01:14:37,452 --> 01:14:38,851
I haven't even told you
about the wedding.

1434
01:14:38,887 --> 01:14:40,320
They loved your present.

1435
01:14:40,355 --> 01:14:42,380
Please don't make me feel guilty.

1436
01:14:42,424 --> 01:14:44,153
Okay, your work
is important to you.

1437
01:14:44,192 --> 01:14:45,659
Okay, but I don't get to choose

1438
01:14:45,694 --> 01:14:47,162
when to take time off; you do.

1439
01:14:47,196 --> 01:14:49,687
So, like, one hour
is all I'm asking for.

1440
01:14:49,732 --> 01:14:51,700
I had a Pakistani once,

1441
01:14:51,734 --> 01:14:53,224
and he was very supportive.

1442
01:15:03,913 --> 01:15:04,971
Hey.

1443
01:15:05,014 --> 01:15:07,107
Hey yourself, werewolf.

1444
01:15:07,150 --> 01:15:10,779
Not sure what's going on
with the beard situation,

1445
01:15:10,820 --> 01:15:14,278
but it's starting to freak
some people out around here.

1446
01:15:14,323 --> 01:15:15,381
I don't understand.

1447
01:15:15,425 --> 01:15:17,086
But Dr. Phil has a mustache.

1448
01:15:19,163 --> 01:15:20,721
What? It reminds me
of where I come from.

1449
01:15:20,764 --> 01:15:22,698
Jerk chicken reminds me
of where I come from,

1450
01:15:22,733 --> 01:15:25,702
but I'm not smearing it
all over my face.

1451
01:15:25,736 --> 01:15:26,998
Maybe you should.

1452
01:15:37,281 --> 01:15:39,272
(door opens)

1453
01:15:42,352 --> 01:15:43,512
(keys clatter)

1454
01:15:47,458 --> 01:15:49,426
(electronic beep)

1455
01:15:49,460 --> 01:15:51,156
You have a message.

1456
01:15:51,196 --> 01:15:52,322
(in Urdu) Happy Eid, son.

1457
01:15:52,363 --> 01:15:53,489
Happy Eid.

1458
01:15:53,531 --> 01:15:55,795
The house is no fun without you.

1459
01:15:55,834 --> 01:15:57,802
There's no power either.

1460
01:15:57,836 --> 01:16:00,031
(in English) We'll eat
in the dark tonight.

1461
01:16:00,071 --> 01:16:01,936
Thinking of you, baita.

1462
01:16:01,973 --> 01:16:03,634
Abu also.

1463
01:16:03,675 --> 01:16:05,609
(in Urdu) Much love.

1464
01:16:05,643 --> 01:16:07,167
(machine beeps)

1465
01:16:08,179 --> 01:16:09,203
(bottle opener clatters)

1466
01:16:18,056 --> 01:16:19,546
Happy Eid.

1467
01:16:21,726 --> 01:16:24,696
(morose orchestral music)

1468
01:16:24,730 --> 01:16:27,198
♪

1469
01:16:27,233 --> 01:16:29,064
Quite a beard.

1470
01:16:29,101 --> 01:16:32,127
That's getting to be some
very serious mullah action.

1471
01:16:33,439 --> 01:16:35,407
I want you to get me
two glasses of the crystal...

1472
01:16:35,441 --> 01:16:36,601
(whispering indistinctly)

1473
01:16:42,081 --> 01:16:44,413
So we've got to evaluate
a prestige publisher

1474
01:16:44,450 --> 01:16:46,042
in Istanbul for a conglomerate.

1475
01:16:46,085 --> 01:16:47,177
And guess what.

1476
01:16:47,219 --> 01:16:48,846
You are the chosen one.

1477
01:16:48,888 --> 01:16:50,788
Thank you.

1478
01:16:50,823 --> 01:16:52,688
The directors agreed with me.

1479
01:16:52,725 --> 01:16:54,853
We're upping you.

1480
01:16:54,895 --> 01:16:56,089
You are the youngest associate

1481
01:16:56,129 --> 01:16:58,063
in the history of Underwood Samson.

1482
01:16:58,098 --> 01:16:59,190
(glasses clink)

1483
01:17:02,569 --> 01:17:06,369
Although, I do believe
appearances are important.

1484
01:17:06,406 --> 01:17:09,204
Success requires...

1485
01:17:09,242 --> 01:17:11,710
some adjustment
in that department.

1486
01:17:15,015 --> 01:17:17,540
Underwood, Samson,

1487
01:17:17,584 --> 01:17:19,677
and The Mighty Khan.

1488
01:17:19,719 --> 01:17:21,186
Oh, no partners.

1489
01:17:21,221 --> 01:17:22,950
Just Khan. I'm a dictator,
remember?

1490
01:17:22,989 --> 01:17:24,013
Mm.

1491
01:17:25,993 --> 01:17:27,460
Motherfucker.

1492
01:17:27,495 --> 01:17:30,020
Next time you want to see me,
call my secretary, okay?

1493
01:17:30,064 --> 01:17:31,224
Up yours.

1494
01:17:42,577 --> 01:17:45,569
(speaking Urdu)

1495
01:17:56,791 --> 01:17:58,259
I'm not going to take
medication!

1496
01:17:58,293 --> 01:17:59,260
911.

1497
01:17:59,294 --> 01:18:00,591
No more medication.

1498
01:18:00,629 --> 01:18:02,494
There's a crazy Arab guy
in midtown Manhattan.

1499
01:18:02,531 --> 01:18:03,828
Long-distance killer!

1500
01:18:03,866 --> 01:18:05,527
Why he get all credit?

1501
01:18:05,567 --> 01:18:07,865
Yeah, 53rd and Lexington.

1502
01:18:07,903 --> 01:18:09,871
Homegrown!

1503
01:18:09,905 --> 01:18:11,338
We are homegrown bombers!

1504
01:18:11,373 --> 01:18:13,170
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
- We're homegrown bombers!

1505
01:18:13,208 --> 01:18:15,108
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
- We are homegrown bomb...

1506
01:18:15,143 --> 01:18:16,474
Bomb your children!

1507
01:18:16,511 --> 01:18:17,773
You bastard!
Hey!

1508
01:18:17,813 --> 01:18:18,780
He's crazy.

1509
01:18:18,814 --> 01:18:21,009
(shouting indistinctly)

1510
01:18:21,049 --> 01:18:25,281
(police sirens wailing)

1511
01:18:25,320 --> 01:18:26,617
(indistinct radio transmission)

1512
01:18:26,655 --> 01:18:28,452
Hey!
Hold up!

1513
01:18:28,490 --> 01:18:30,459
You in the black coat,
stop right there.

1514
01:18:30,493 --> 01:18:31,790
- I didn't do...
- Hands on the car.

1515
01:18:31,828 --> 01:18:33,625
- I didn't do anything.
- Put your hands on the car.

1516
01:18:33,663 --> 01:18:35,187
The guy you're looking for
is back there.

1517
01:18:35,231 --> 01:18:36,391
Yeah, we'll get him.

1518
01:18:36,432 --> 01:18:37,990
- I work on the 53rd floor...
- Hands down.

1519
01:18:38,034 --> 01:18:39,558
Of that building,
Underwood Samson.

1520
01:18:39,602 --> 01:18:41,365
Why don't you just check?

1521
01:18:41,404 --> 01:18:42,928
Why don't you just...

1522
01:18:42,972 --> 01:18:44,462
- Officer, please.
- Spread your legs!

1523
01:18:44,507 --> 01:18:46,737
You got any weapons on you?

1524
01:18:46,776 --> 01:18:48,038
Don't do this, man.

1525
01:18:48,077 --> 01:18:50,602
Ain't doing nothing
but my job, little man.

1526
01:18:50,647 --> 01:18:53,639
(police siren wailing)

1527
01:18:55,852 --> 01:18:57,114
Ow, man!

1528
01:18:57,153 --> 01:18:59,678
Uh-uh!
Get your hands off me!

1529
01:18:59,722 --> 01:19:00,849
Uh!

1530
01:19:04,194 --> 01:19:05,286
Wait right here.

1531
01:19:06,463 --> 01:19:08,021
(door buzzes)

1532
01:19:31,789 --> 01:19:33,382
I'm Special Agent Ford.

1533
01:19:33,425 --> 01:19:34,790
This is Special Agent Jackson.

1534
01:19:34,826 --> 01:19:35,918
This is inexcusable.

1535
01:19:35,961 --> 01:19:37,622
I'd like to see my lawyer, please.

1536
01:19:43,101 --> 01:19:45,160
Are you refusing to talk
to us?

1537
01:19:45,203 --> 01:19:46,670
No, you picked up
the wrong guy,

1538
01:19:46,705 --> 01:19:47,763
and I'm sick of this shit.

1539
01:19:47,806 --> 01:19:50,798
I want to see my lawyer.

1540
01:19:50,842 --> 01:19:52,935
You ever been to the Philippines?

1541
01:19:57,582 --> 01:20:00,142
I work at Underwood Samson.

1542
01:20:00,185 --> 01:20:03,518
I was inspecting a company there
as a financial analyst.

1543
01:20:04,957 --> 01:20:08,449
You ever had any combat
training in Afghanistan?

1544
01:20:12,732 --> 01:20:14,461
Of course I've never had
combat training,

1545
01:20:14,500 --> 01:20:16,764
and I've never set foot
in Afghanistan!

1546
01:20:16,802 --> 01:20:18,030
Don't get upset.

1547
01:20:18,070 --> 01:20:19,697
I am upset. I'm upset
about my treatment.

1548
01:20:19,739 --> 01:20:21,070
I'm not a fucking terrorist.

1549
01:20:24,777 --> 01:20:27,712
Have you ever been a member
of a terrorist organization?

1550
01:20:27,747 --> 01:20:29,009
Okay, you know what?

1551
01:20:29,048 --> 01:20:31,346
I'm sick of having to try
and prove a negative,

1552
01:20:31,384 --> 01:20:33,284
so why don't you either
charge me with something

1553
01:20:33,319 --> 01:20:34,809
or let me go?

1554
01:20:40,927 --> 01:20:43,088
How do you feel about the
United States of America?

1555
01:20:50,070 --> 01:20:51,697
Agent Ford,

1556
01:20:51,738 --> 01:20:54,400
I love the United States of America.

1557
01:20:58,245 --> 01:21:00,372
Hey, baby, I can't wait to see you

1558
01:21:00,414 --> 01:21:02,006
at my opening tonight.

1559
01:21:02,049 --> 01:21:05,576
And the gallery's on the corner
of Crosby and Prince.

1560
01:21:05,619 --> 01:21:06,950
Okay, I'll see you.

1561
01:21:08,256 --> 01:21:09,848
(police siren wailing)

1562
01:21:09,891 --> 01:21:11,791
Hey, Marina!

1563
01:21:11,826 --> 01:21:13,623
Hi, sugar.

1564
01:21:13,661 --> 01:21:16,653
(indistinct conversations)

1565
01:21:23,171 --> 01:21:25,036
I'm alone.

1566
01:21:25,073 --> 01:21:28,600
I'm very, very alone.

1567
01:21:28,643 --> 01:21:31,203
(indistinct recording)

1568
01:21:31,245 --> 01:21:33,008
I want to forget.

1569
01:21:35,683 --> 01:21:37,310
Ladies and gentlemen, a reminder:

1570
01:21:37,351 --> 01:21:39,286
never accept a parcel or bag

1571
01:21:39,321 --> 01:21:41,687
from a third party
for any reason.

1572
01:21:49,598 --> 01:21:51,259
I want to forget.

1573
01:21:52,501 --> 01:21:54,833
Never leave your baggage
unattended.

1574
01:21:56,405 --> 01:21:58,396
- Hors d'oeuvres?
- Oh, no, I'm vegan.

1575
01:21:58,440 --> 01:22:01,432
(indistinct conversations)

1576
01:22:03,979 --> 01:22:06,277
I had a Pakistani once...

1577
01:22:14,457 --> 01:22:16,925
I'm glad... I'm glad
you're enjoying it.

1578
01:22:16,960 --> 01:22:18,689
Good to see you.

1579
01:22:18,728 --> 01:22:19,922
- Hi.
- Hi.

1580
01:22:19,963 --> 01:22:21,225
- Hi.
- Good to see you.

1581
01:22:21,264 --> 01:22:22,663
Ah.

1582
01:22:22,699 --> 01:22:25,259
- This is amazing.
- Thank you.

1583
01:22:25,301 --> 01:22:26,768
Changez?

1584
01:22:26,803 --> 01:22:27,963
Changez!

1585
01:22:33,076 --> 01:22:35,874
I'm so happy you're here.

1586
01:22:35,912 --> 01:22:38,642
I don't recognize my
own voice anymore.

1587
01:22:38,681 --> 01:22:39,978
What have you done?

1588
01:22:40,016 --> 01:22:42,383
It's... what do you mean?

1589
01:22:42,419 --> 01:22:43,579
This is us.

1590
01:22:45,122 --> 01:22:46,817
It's about us.

1591
01:22:46,857 --> 01:22:48,188
From you too now?

1592
01:22:50,961 --> 01:22:53,429
You're the one goddamn person
I trusted in this city,

1593
01:22:53,464 --> 01:22:55,762
and now I get this shit,

1594
01:22:55,799 --> 01:22:58,427
this fucking shit
from you too now?

1595
01:23:02,139 --> 01:23:03,265
Hmm?
- I don't...

1596
01:23:03,307 --> 01:23:05,207
I thought... I thought...

1597
01:23:05,242 --> 01:23:06,834
I thought you'd be proud of me.

1598
01:23:06,877 --> 01:23:08,105
- Why would I be proud?
What?

1599
01:23:08,145 --> 01:23:11,137
Proud of being your own
little pet artistic project?

1600
01:23:11,182 --> 01:23:12,513
Can we please take this outside?

1601
01:23:12,550 --> 01:23:14,314
- No, what?
Was that the idea?

1602
01:23:14,352 --> 01:23:15,979
Huh?
How chic! How chic!

1603
01:23:16,021 --> 01:23:18,956
"I'm gonna date a Pakistani
after 9/11,

1604
01:23:18,990 --> 01:23:21,220
and it's gonna be great
for my bohemian street cred. "

1605
01:23:21,259 --> 01:23:23,056
Is that the idea?
- That's completely unfair.

1606
01:23:23,094 --> 01:23:26,825
"I fucked the 20th hijacker"?
Huh?

1607
01:23:26,865 --> 01:23:29,857
I'm like the ultimate downtown
status symbol right now.

1608
01:23:31,069 --> 01:23:33,037
Is that it? You're just
gonna walk away?

1609
01:23:33,071 --> 01:23:34,595
That's all you got to say
for yourself?

1610
01:23:34,639 --> 01:23:37,767
I mean, are your feelings so pure?

1611
01:23:37,809 --> 01:23:39,242
Would you have
been interested in me

1612
01:23:39,277 --> 01:23:40,710
if my uncle wasn't your CEO

1613
01:23:40,745 --> 01:23:44,613
or if my mother lived in Queens
instead of Park and 85th?

1614
01:23:44,649 --> 01:23:46,447
- Are you kidding me?
You're a sick girl.

1615
01:23:46,485 --> 01:23:47,850
It was never about that for me!

1616
01:23:47,887 --> 01:23:49,047
You might not believe this,

1617
01:23:49,088 --> 01:23:50,885
but that is an expression of love.

1618
01:23:50,923 --> 01:23:53,016
- You know what it is?
That... that is defamation.

1619
01:23:53,059 --> 01:23:54,117
I want it taken down.

1620
01:23:54,160 --> 01:23:55,627
Changez, please.

1621
01:23:57,296 --> 01:23:59,856
Please, just take a breath.

1622
01:23:59,899 --> 01:24:01,526
I can't believe
you're reacting this way.

1623
01:24:01,567 --> 01:24:02,693
How do you want me to react?

1624
01:24:02,735 --> 01:24:03,724
Please take a breath.

1625
01:24:03,769 --> 01:24:04,997
How could you do that?

1626
01:24:05,037 --> 01:24:06,163
Stop attacking me!

1627
01:24:06,205 --> 01:24:07,763
Stop attacking me
for one minute!

1628
01:24:07,807 --> 01:24:09,900
Please stop attacking me!
Please!

1629
01:24:09,942 --> 01:24:12,240
Please stop attacking me!

1630
01:24:12,278 --> 01:24:15,179
You could do it because
you're reckless.

1631
01:24:15,214 --> 01:24:17,877
You're reckless enough
to drive drunk

1632
01:24:17,918 --> 01:24:19,943
with the person
you supposedly love

1633
01:24:19,987 --> 01:24:21,955
sitting in the passenger seat.

1634
01:24:21,989 --> 01:24:23,149
Oh...

1635
01:24:25,492 --> 01:24:26,618
(sobs)

1636
01:24:32,833 --> 01:24:34,528
Oh, I didn't know...

1637
01:24:34,568 --> 01:24:37,662
I didn't know you could
be capable of such cruelty.

1638
01:24:59,927 --> 01:25:01,087
Well...

1639
01:25:09,704 --> 01:25:12,229
(indistinct conversation)

1640
01:25:12,273 --> 01:25:14,264
(crying)

1641
01:25:20,883 --> 01:25:23,852
(dramatic music)

1642
01:25:23,886 --> 01:25:29,279
♪

1643
01:25:44,206 --> 01:25:45,605
The holding company acquired

1644
01:25:45,641 --> 01:25:47,302
Basak Yayimci Publishing
nine years ago.

1645
01:25:47,343 --> 01:25:48,605
It used to be a classy press,

1646
01:25:48,644 --> 01:25:49,770
but it's hemorrhaging money,

1647
01:25:49,812 --> 01:25:51,211
and we need to stop the bleeding.

1648
01:25:58,254 --> 01:26:00,779
Nazmi Kemal will not
be happy to see us.

1649
01:26:06,830 --> 01:26:09,162
For 42 years,

1650
01:26:09,199 --> 01:26:10,689
I've made books.

1651
01:26:12,402 --> 01:26:15,394
And through this press,

1652
01:26:15,438 --> 01:26:17,406
the greatest Middle Eastern writers

1653
01:26:17,440 --> 01:26:19,738
have given their stories to the world.

1654
01:26:22,045 --> 01:26:24,480
And you've come here
to render me obsolete.

1655
01:26:25,783 --> 01:26:29,617
I have great respect for
the work of publishers.

1656
01:26:29,653 --> 01:26:32,918
I've valued half a dozen or so
over the last ten years.

1657
01:26:36,894 --> 01:26:39,158
Are you qualified to value me?

1658
01:26:41,065 --> 01:26:42,123
(chuckles)

1659
01:26:47,204 --> 01:26:49,001
Well, no one can put a value

1660
01:26:49,039 --> 01:26:50,597
on what you've accomplished here.

1661
01:26:52,910 --> 01:26:54,434
My father is a poet.

1662
01:26:54,478 --> 01:26:55,706
He's well known in the Punjab.

1663
01:26:55,746 --> 01:26:57,578
His greatest friend is his publisher.

1664
01:26:59,918 --> 01:27:02,751
You are a keeper of our culture
in this part of the world.

1665
01:27:03,855 --> 01:27:05,288
Your father is a poet?

1666
01:27:11,263 --> 01:27:14,562
I think you should be ashamed
of yourself,

1667
01:27:14,599 --> 01:27:17,932
doing what you're doing here.

1668
01:27:20,005 --> 01:27:21,905
Right.

1669
01:27:21,940 --> 01:27:24,135
If you'll excuse us,
we need to use your office.

1670
01:27:26,945 --> 01:27:28,174
The accounts you asked for.

1671
01:27:28,214 --> 01:27:29,155
Thank you.

1672
01:27:29,808 --> 01:27:30,744
Thank you.

1673
01:27:34,854 --> 01:27:36,321
Last two years.

1674
01:27:36,355 --> 01:27:37,413
Right.

1675
01:27:45,865 --> 01:27:46,923
Take these figures,

1676
01:27:46,966 --> 01:27:48,934
discount it to the net
present value.

1677
01:27:48,968 --> 01:27:50,128
What's the ROA?

1678
01:27:52,505 --> 01:27:53,665
Zero.

1679
01:27:57,343 --> 01:27:58,605
I'll call London.

1680
01:28:03,717 --> 01:28:06,686
(melancholy music)

1681
01:28:06,720 --> 01:28:12,107
♪

1682
01:28:23,937 --> 01:28:26,929
(man chanting)

1683
01:28:41,322 --> 01:28:47,290
♪

1684
01:29:06,849 --> 01:29:12,583
♪

1685
01:29:20,462 --> 01:29:23,454
(birds calling)

1686
01:29:30,706 --> 01:29:31,866
Changez.

1687
01:29:33,609 --> 01:29:34,770
Look what I found.

1688
01:29:38,181 --> 01:29:39,944
Part of an anthology

1689
01:29:39,983 --> 01:29:42,281
of contemporary poets
from the Punjab.

1690
01:29:43,420 --> 01:29:45,411
Your father is Ajmal Khan, correct?

1691
01:29:46,990 --> 01:29:48,150
(scoffs softly)

1692
01:29:52,529 --> 01:29:55,589
I didn't realize he'd been
translated into Turkish.

1693
01:29:55,632 --> 01:29:56,792
That's for you.

1694
01:29:58,101 --> 01:29:59,227
Thank you very much.

1695
01:30:04,207 --> 01:30:06,141
Would you care to join
me for lunch?

1696
01:30:07,912 --> 01:30:08,970
Sure.

1697
01:30:20,891 --> 01:30:22,882
Have you heard
of the Janissaries?

1698
01:30:25,563 --> 01:30:26,723
No.

1699
01:30:30,668 --> 01:30:32,295
They were Christian boys

1700
01:30:32,336 --> 01:30:34,998
captured by the Ottomans

1701
01:30:35,039 --> 01:30:37,633
to be soldiers in the
mighty Muslim army.

1702
01:30:40,646 --> 01:30:44,207
When they came of age,

1703
01:30:44,249 --> 01:30:46,717
they were sent to kill
their former families

1704
01:30:46,752 --> 01:30:48,743
and destroy
their former homes.

1705
01:30:54,760 --> 01:30:56,751
How old were you when
you went to America?

1706
01:30:58,563 --> 01:31:00,690
I was 18.

1707
01:31:00,732 --> 01:31:02,825
Ah.
Much older.

1708
01:31:07,506 --> 01:31:10,101
The Janissaries were always
taken in childhood.

1709
01:31:11,244 --> 01:31:14,213
And when they became men,

1710
01:31:14,247 --> 01:31:17,341
they were devoted
to their new caretakers

1711
01:31:17,383 --> 01:31:19,112
to serve their adopted empire.

1712
01:31:19,152 --> 01:31:21,382
I'm not devoted to the empire.

1713
01:31:21,421 --> 01:31:22,513
Mm.

1714
01:31:31,164 --> 01:31:32,597
I apologize for my demeanor.

1715
01:31:32,632 --> 01:31:35,157
I'm working through some
personal matters at the moment.

1716
01:31:35,201 --> 01:31:36,361
A woman.

1717
01:31:40,206 --> 01:31:43,506
Young men don't make
good mercenaries.

1718
01:31:43,544 --> 01:31:45,205
They need a cause to fight.

1719
01:31:48,749 --> 01:31:49,875
May I?

1720
01:31:54,121 --> 01:31:55,213
Mm.

1721
01:32:00,928 --> 01:32:03,726
When you determine
where you stand,

1722
01:32:03,764 --> 01:32:05,789
the color will return
to your world.

1723
01:32:07,634 --> 01:32:10,432
I'm not so hopeful about
the color returning to mine.

1724
01:32:16,578 --> 01:32:19,570
(children singing indistinctly)

1725
01:32:21,916 --> 01:32:24,885
(melancholy music)

1726
01:32:24,919 --> 01:32:30,249
♪

1727
01:32:46,408 --> 01:32:47,875
Hey.

1728
01:32:47,910 --> 01:32:49,241
Good news.

1729
01:32:49,278 --> 01:32:51,712
London gave us the green light
to terminate Nazmi Kemal

1730
01:32:51,747 --> 01:32:53,715
and shutter the offices here.

1731
01:32:53,749 --> 01:32:57,014
They want us to take care of it
because we're here in person.

1732
01:32:57,052 --> 01:32:59,350
So do you want the honors

1733
01:32:59,388 --> 01:33:00,878
or should I?

1734
01:33:02,091 --> 01:33:04,059
I'll do it.

1735
01:33:04,093 --> 01:33:05,253
In the morning?

1736
01:33:05,294 --> 01:33:06,556
Good.

1737
01:33:06,595 --> 01:33:08,290
Get back to me
as soon as you're done.

1738
01:33:08,330 --> 01:33:09,661
Get some rest.
- Okay.

1739
01:33:15,504 --> 01:33:19,202
I imagined
those Janissary boys, uprooted,

1740
01:33:19,242 --> 01:33:22,268
landing in new homes
with new fathers...

1741
01:33:22,312 --> 01:33:24,610
some of them good fathers...

1742
01:33:24,648 --> 01:33:27,014
their loyalties terribly divided.

1743
01:33:29,052 --> 01:33:31,282
You're deluding yourself that
you have this role here.

1744
01:33:31,321 --> 01:33:32,811
You don't.

1745
01:33:32,856 --> 01:33:34,653
You don't.
Go home, Bobby.

1746
01:33:35,659 --> 01:33:36,658
Go home?

1747
01:33:37,888 --> 01:33:39,083
Go home?

1748
01:33:39,696 --> 01:33:40,924
Do you have any fucking idea

1749
01:33:40,964 --> 01:33:42,556
what happens to your family
if I go home?

1750
01:33:42,599 --> 01:33:43,725
Huh?

1751
01:33:43,767 --> 01:33:44,995
Once they snatch you

1752
01:33:45,035 --> 01:33:49,700
and drop your ass in a cell
in Peshawar...

1753
01:33:49,740 --> 01:33:51,298
Seven more students arrested.

1754
01:33:51,342 --> 01:33:52,331
We must protest.

1755
01:33:52,376 --> 01:33:55,368
(indistinct chatter)

1756
01:33:59,684 --> 01:34:01,208
Brothers, please listen!

1757
01:34:01,252 --> 01:34:02,514
Everyone, listen to me!

1758
01:34:02,553 --> 01:34:05,716
Hussain, do what you must,

1759
01:34:05,756 --> 01:34:07,553
but do it peacefully.

1760
01:34:07,592 --> 01:34:09,389
Remember, no violence.

1761
01:34:09,427 --> 01:34:11,691
- Sir, observing situation.
Stand by.

1762
01:34:11,729 --> 01:34:12,855
Copy that.

1763
01:34:12,897 --> 01:34:15,866
(ominous music)

1764
01:34:15,900 --> 01:34:19,802
♪

1765
01:34:19,838 --> 01:34:21,965
You know, my capacity
for evaluation

1766
01:34:22,007 --> 01:34:23,440
hasn't diminished, Bobby.

1767
01:34:23,475 --> 01:34:25,739
You know what I see before me?

1768
01:34:25,777 --> 01:34:29,406
I see a man with hash
under his fingernails

1769
01:34:29,448 --> 01:34:32,849
who likely smokes it alone.

1770
01:34:32,885 --> 01:34:34,648
I see the odd white man

1771
01:34:34,686 --> 01:34:36,745
who lives in the old quarter

1772
01:34:36,788 --> 01:34:37,948
and only ventures out

1773
01:34:37,990 --> 01:34:40,254
to buy local food
and local girls...

1774
01:34:41,960 --> 01:34:43,257
Who's been here so long

1775
01:34:43,295 --> 01:34:44,990
his own blood family
have forgotten him.

1776
01:34:45,030 --> 01:34:47,021
And there's nobody here
to replace them.

1777
01:34:48,333 --> 01:34:50,301
You're playing a dangerous game,
Changez.

1778
01:34:50,335 --> 01:34:53,430
- I'm sorry.
I'm just...

1779
01:34:53,473 --> 01:34:56,465
I'm telling you something

1780
01:34:56,509 --> 01:34:58,773
that it took me a long time
to realize.

1781
01:35:00,280 --> 01:35:01,941
Some truths take their time.

1782
01:35:07,353 --> 01:35:09,617
I was just coming to see you.

1783
01:35:09,656 --> 01:35:11,783
Interesting message you left me.

1784
01:35:11,824 --> 01:35:13,849
You're not letting him go?
What the hell does that mean?

1785
01:35:13,893 --> 01:35:17,294
It means that I'm not
gonna fire Nazmi Kemal.

1786
01:35:17,330 --> 01:35:20,629
And, in fact, I'm not gonna do
any more evaluations.

1787
01:35:20,667 --> 01:35:22,134
I'm quitting the firm, Jim.

1788
01:35:22,168 --> 01:35:23,761
You accepted the position
of associate

1789
01:35:23,804 --> 01:35:24,998
less than three months ago.

1790
01:35:25,039 --> 01:35:27,098
You leave now,
you'll be giving up all hope

1791
01:35:27,141 --> 01:35:29,075
of ever doing this kind of work
again anywhere.

1792
01:35:29,109 --> 01:35:31,043
You'd be committing
professional suicide.

1793
01:35:32,479 --> 01:35:34,242
I know I've let you down, Jim,

1794
01:35:34,281 --> 01:35:36,215
and I'm deeply sorry for that.

1795
01:35:36,250 --> 01:35:38,480
But I have to tell you
that I'm through.

1796
01:35:38,519 --> 01:35:39,747
You're telling me?

1797
01:35:39,787 --> 01:35:40,981
You don't tell me!

1798
01:35:41,021 --> 01:35:42,079
Can we be civil, Jim?

1799
01:35:42,122 --> 01:35:43,817
You think you're the only person

1800
01:35:43,857 --> 01:35:46,451
who's experienced
injustice firsthand?

1801
01:35:46,493 --> 01:35:48,256
Throw a rock out there
anywhere in this city,

1802
01:35:48,295 --> 01:35:49,762
and it'll land on the grave
of someone

1803
01:35:49,797 --> 01:35:51,287
who's seen worse than you.

1804
01:35:51,332 --> 01:35:54,096
Now, maybe you're having
some kind of a breakdown.

1805
01:35:54,134 --> 01:35:56,228
I will see to it that you
will get some rest

1806
01:35:56,271 --> 01:35:57,533
after this is done.

1807
01:35:57,572 --> 01:35:59,369
But you will treat
my commitment to you

1808
01:35:59,407 --> 01:36:02,171
with the respect
that it deserves!

1809
01:36:02,210 --> 01:36:04,770
And to myself as well.

1810
01:36:04,813 --> 01:36:07,373
I have a commitment to myself.

1811
01:36:08,717 --> 01:36:11,117
Do you want to be an insurance
salesman, Changez,

1812
01:36:11,152 --> 01:36:12,380
with a mortgage
and a migraine?

1813
01:36:12,420 --> 01:36:14,115
Is that the life you envision
for yourself?

1814
01:36:14,155 --> 01:36:15,179
As opposed to what?

1815
01:36:15,223 --> 01:36:17,248
I have to live in truth.

1816
01:36:17,292 --> 01:36:18,759
You taught me, Jim.

1817
01:36:18,793 --> 01:36:20,124
You put your fucking shoes on,

1818
01:36:20,161 --> 01:36:21,423
and you go down to that office,

1819
01:36:21,463 --> 01:36:24,023
and you do the job
you were hired to do!

1820
01:36:27,970 --> 01:36:29,460
It's not my job anymore.

1821
01:36:32,708 --> 01:36:35,677
(brooding rock music)

1822
01:36:35,711 --> 01:36:37,372
♪

1823
01:36:37,413 --> 01:36:41,372
♪ Hear me out, O, Lord... ♪

1824
01:36:41,417 --> 01:36:45,353
♪

1825
01:36:45,388 --> 01:36:49,347
♪ It was you, true Lord, who said... ♪

1826
01:36:49,392 --> 01:36:53,385
♪

1827
01:36:53,429 --> 01:36:57,388
♪ Man, you are king of the world... ♪

1828
01:36:57,433 --> 01:37:03,365
♪

1829
01:37:09,880 --> 01:37:12,178
What's he gonna do?

1830
01:37:12,215 --> 01:37:13,341
About time.

1831
01:37:13,383 --> 01:37:18,090
♪

1832
01:37:19,856 --> 01:37:21,016
Fidel.

1833
01:37:23,260 --> 01:37:25,160
Is this about me beating you
in basketball?

1834
01:37:25,195 --> 01:37:26,287
(chuckles)

1835
01:37:29,366 --> 01:37:31,494
You're gonna be a great analyst,
Wainwright.

1836
01:37:33,805 --> 01:37:35,830
What are you gonna be?

1837
01:37:35,873 --> 01:37:40,503
♪

1838
01:37:40,545 --> 01:37:42,172
Yes, I read the perspectives,
and more importantly...

1839
01:37:42,213 --> 01:37:46,013
♪ A fine king You made,
O Lord... ♪

1840
01:37:46,050 --> 01:37:50,111
♪

1841
01:37:50,154 --> 01:37:54,113
♪ Who endures life's blows
with grace... ♪

1842
01:37:54,158 --> 01:37:57,423
♪

1843
01:37:57,462 --> 01:38:01,660
♪ I don't want this kingdom, Lord... ♪

1844
01:38:01,699 --> 01:38:05,898
♪

1845
01:38:05,938 --> 01:38:09,897
♪ All I want is a grain of respect... ♪

1846
01:38:09,942 --> 01:38:15,152
♪

1847
01:38:21,386 --> 01:38:24,446
♪ Hear me out, O Lord ♪

1848
01:38:24,490 --> 01:38:28,449
♪ Heed my plea,
and I'll heed Yours... ♪

1849
01:38:28,494 --> 01:38:34,058
♪

1850
01:38:34,100 --> 01:38:36,864
(knocking at door)

1851
01:38:36,903 --> 01:38:40,930
♪ Curse me if I break this vow... ♪

1852
01:38:40,974 --> 01:38:45,707
♪ If this pact displeases You... ♪

1853
01:38:45,745 --> 01:38:49,704
♪ Then let me find
another God... ♪

1854
01:38:49,749 --> 01:38:55,281
♪

1855
01:38:56,589 --> 01:38:57,715
(sighs)

1856
01:38:59,025 --> 01:39:00,515
- Hey.
- Hi.

1857
01:39:06,734 --> 01:39:09,567
Ah, you're...
you're moving.

1858
01:39:12,072 --> 01:39:13,164
Yeah.

1859
01:39:19,113 --> 01:39:20,205
(sighs)

1860
01:39:21,649 --> 01:39:24,641
I should have told you
what I'd been working on.

1861
01:39:26,554 --> 01:39:28,351
I wanted to let you in
more than I did.

1862
01:39:28,389 --> 01:39:31,017
It's just, everything
about falling in love with you,

1863
01:39:31,058 --> 01:39:33,891
Changez, it hurt so much.

1864
01:39:37,766 --> 01:39:39,427
- It's okay.
I understand.

1865
01:39:42,137 --> 01:39:43,365
I'm sorry about what I said.

1866
01:39:43,405 --> 01:39:44,463
Oh.

1867
01:39:55,217 --> 01:39:57,947
You're going back to Pakistan?

1868
01:39:57,986 --> 01:39:59,681
I have no job, no visa.

1869
01:39:59,721 --> 01:40:01,882
I have to leave the country
within two weeks.

1870
01:40:04,125 --> 01:40:05,285
You want to come?

1871
01:40:14,036 --> 01:40:15,196
Yes.

1872
01:40:20,943 --> 01:40:23,275
But my iddat isn't over yet.

1873
01:40:26,682 --> 01:40:29,651
(rueful flute music)

1874
01:40:29,685 --> 01:40:35,382
♪

1875
01:40:48,338 --> 01:40:51,307
(man singing in Urdu)

1876
01:40:51,341 --> 01:40:56,432
♪

1877
01:41:20,004 --> 01:41:21,164
(glass shatters)

1878
01:41:23,007 --> 01:41:25,976
(brooding rock music)

1879
