(sobbing)

1881
01:41:34,719 --> 01:41:40,567
♪

1882
01:42:04,483 --> 01:42:06,314
You haven't eaten in two days.

1883
01:42:42,288 --> 01:42:43,653
Good to see you, Mr. Khan.

1884
01:42:43,690 --> 01:42:45,487
And you, Professor Rainier.

1885
01:42:45,525 --> 01:42:48,495
We've experienced an exodus
of foreign professors

1886
01:42:48,529 --> 01:42:51,464
from Lahore in the past
several months.

1887
01:42:51,499 --> 01:42:53,160
I need an answer quickly.

1888
01:42:55,202 --> 01:42:57,466
So two months ago,

1889
01:42:57,505 --> 01:42:59,473
I was sitting in my office

1890
01:42:59,507 --> 01:43:02,408
on the 53rd floor of a
Manhattan skyscraper.

1891
01:43:02,443 --> 01:43:04,377
I was living my dream...

1892
01:43:04,412 --> 01:43:05,606
the American dream.

1893
01:43:06,814 --> 01:43:08,782
So now I'm back.

1894
01:43:08,816 --> 01:43:10,181
What I'd like your help with is,

1895
01:43:10,217 --> 01:43:14,347
is there a Pakistani dream?

1896
01:43:20,929 --> 01:43:22,590
One that doesn't involve emigrating.

1897
01:43:27,369 --> 01:43:29,837
It seems we...

1898
01:43:29,871 --> 01:43:32,339
we put out our begging bowl
to other countries.

1899
01:43:32,374 --> 01:43:34,672
We do exactly
what they tell us to do,

1900
01:43:34,709 --> 01:43:36,939
and then we despise them for it.

1901
01:43:36,978 --> 01:43:39,003
After a while, we start
to despise ourselves for it.

1902
01:43:39,047 --> 01:43:40,105
I know I did.

1903
01:43:40,148 --> 01:43:42,912
If we wish to be self-reliant...

1904
01:43:42,951 --> 01:43:44,646
We need to talk about taxes.

1905
01:43:44,686 --> 01:43:47,450
So you were talking
about options.

1906
01:43:47,489 --> 01:43:49,719
What are the options
for Pakistan right now?

1907
01:43:51,394 --> 01:43:53,692
Would you like to join us
at one of our meetings?

1908
01:43:55,698 --> 01:43:56,824
If you look at the stats,

1909
01:43:56,866 --> 01:43:58,800
we don't actually tax
our population.

1910
01:43:58,835 --> 01:44:00,427
So let's start
on the national level,

1911
01:44:00,470 --> 01:44:02,404
and we'll break it down to personal.

1912
01:44:02,438 --> 01:44:05,430
(applause)

1913
01:44:05,475 --> 01:44:07,067
The only way the government...
- Khan.

1914
01:44:07,109 --> 01:44:10,101
(both speaking Urdu)

1915
01:44:14,484 --> 01:44:16,850
I'd like to introduce Mustafa Fazil.

1916
01:44:16,886 --> 01:44:18,877
This is Professor Changez Khan.

1917
01:44:18,921 --> 01:44:21,913
(phone buzzing)

1918
01:44:29,967 --> 01:44:31,958
(buzzing continues)

1919
01:44:39,176 --> 01:44:40,734
Talk to me, Bobby.
What's going on?

1920
01:44:40,777 --> 01:44:42,938
It's called progress.
It takes time.

1921
01:44:42,980 --> 01:44:44,777
Time's up, pal.
I've got to get you out of here.

1922
01:44:44,815 --> 01:44:47,306
I don't need a second American
kidnapped today.

1923
01:44:47,351 --> 01:44:50,081
Students, cooperate
with the police or else!

1924
01:44:50,120 --> 01:44:52,247
Free the students!

1925
01:44:52,289 --> 01:44:55,316
Out, America, out!

1926
01:44:55,360 --> 01:44:58,329
(people shouting)

1927
01:44:59,697 --> 01:45:01,289
- Sir, are you all right?
- Yeah...

1928
01:45:01,332 --> 01:45:03,527
The students are fired up.
It's explosive.

1929
01:45:03,568 --> 01:45:04,796
If you come busting in here now,

1930
01:45:04,836 --> 01:45:06,303
you're gonna blow everything.

1931
01:45:06,337 --> 01:45:07,804
He's gonna lead us to Fazil.
I know it.

1932
01:45:07,839 --> 01:45:09,466
If you don't have a location
on Rainier,

1933
01:45:09,507 --> 01:45:11,498
we're wasting time;
I'm coming in.

1934
01:45:11,543 --> 01:45:13,340
I need you to go out there
and keep them calm for me.

1935
01:45:13,378 --> 01:45:14,572
They don't listen to me.

1936
01:45:14,612 --> 01:45:16,443
And your family is really
worried about you.

1937
01:45:16,481 --> 01:45:18,210
Tell them I'm fine.

1938
01:45:18,249 --> 01:45:19,614
Phone them.

1939
01:45:19,651 --> 01:45:20,618
Stay low.

1940
01:45:20,652 --> 01:45:21,778
Cooper, no.

1941
01:45:21,819 --> 01:45:23,548
Coop?

1942
01:45:23,588 --> 01:45:24,714
We're going in!

1943
01:45:28,027 --> 01:45:29,756
Everything okay?

1944
01:45:29,795 --> 01:45:30,887
What's going on?

1945
01:45:30,930 --> 01:45:32,056
It's okay.

1946
01:45:34,366 --> 01:45:35,424
We need to talk...

1947
01:45:37,136 --> 01:45:38,262
Alone.

1948
01:45:41,040 --> 01:45:44,009
(tense music)

1949
01:45:44,043 --> 01:45:46,341
♪

1950
01:45:46,378 --> 01:45:48,505
(people shouting)

1951
01:45:48,547 --> 01:45:51,539
(guns clicking)

1952
01:45:53,352 --> 01:45:54,546
Are the police cooperating?

1953
01:45:54,587 --> 01:45:55,747
Don't count on it.

1954
01:45:58,625 --> 01:46:00,286
Go! Go!
Go!

1955
01:46:00,327 --> 01:46:02,261
Go, go, go!

1956
01:46:02,295 --> 01:46:05,287
(people shouting)

1957
01:46:09,669 --> 01:46:11,432
We need to talk about Anse Rainier.

1958
01:46:11,471 --> 01:46:12,665
Okay, let's talk about him.

1959
01:46:12,706 --> 01:46:14,333
Have you seen all the rumors
in the newspapers?

1960
01:46:14,374 --> 01:46:16,239
Do you know what the students
are saying about him?

1961
01:46:16,276 --> 01:46:17,402
Look, Changez,

1962
01:46:17,444 --> 01:46:19,241
an extraction team
is on their way here.

1963
01:46:19,279 --> 01:46:20,576
If you don't give me something...

1964
01:46:20,614 --> 01:46:21,774
Call it off!

1965
01:46:24,484 --> 01:46:25,542
Bobby, what do you think

1966
01:46:25,585 --> 01:46:27,109
is going to happen
when they get here?

1967
01:46:27,153 --> 01:46:30,180
Do you think all these young men
are just gonna stand idly by?

1968
01:46:30,224 --> 01:46:31,350
all: Out, police, out!

1969
01:46:31,392 --> 01:46:32,586
Out, police, out!

1970
01:46:32,627 --> 01:46:33,651
Huh?

1971
01:46:33,694 --> 01:46:34,956
You need to ask yourself
if you think

1972
01:46:34,996 --> 01:46:37,487
all those lives are worth
risking to save one.

1973
01:46:38,833 --> 01:46:40,323
Who is Anse Rainier?

1974
01:46:40,368 --> 01:46:41,528
(chuckles)

1975
01:46:41,569 --> 01:46:43,901
He's an academic.

1976
01:46:43,938 --> 01:46:46,031
He teaches English to orphans
on his day off.

1977
01:46:46,073 --> 01:46:49,099
The guy doesn't have
a violent bone in his body.

1978
01:46:49,143 --> 01:46:51,771
He read my galleys
for the Massoud book.

1979
01:46:51,812 --> 01:46:54,337
He's a friend, a mentor,
like Jim Cross was to you.

1980
01:46:54,382 --> 01:46:55,747
If that's true, Bobby,

1981
01:46:55,783 --> 01:46:58,274
you should think very carefully
about who your friends are.

1982
01:47:00,087 --> 01:47:01,350
The only way the government...

1983
01:47:01,390 --> 01:47:03,381
(speaking Urdu)

1984
01:47:05,494 --> 01:47:06,756
Salaam.

1985
01:47:06,795 --> 01:47:08,524
(speaking Urdu)

1986
01:47:08,563 --> 01:47:11,589
So you were in America when
they attacked Afghanistan.

1987
01:47:11,633 --> 01:47:12,657
Yes.

1988
01:47:12,701 --> 01:47:14,168
How did you feel

1989
01:47:14,202 --> 01:47:16,295
when you saw the bombs dropping

1990
01:47:16,338 --> 01:47:18,363
on your brothers and sisters?

1991
01:47:19,374 --> 01:47:20,534
I felt angry.

1992
01:47:21,743 --> 01:47:24,803
Yeah, Americans speak of equality,

1993
01:47:24,846 --> 01:47:29,545
then take 100 Muslim lives
to avenge 1 life of their own.

1994
01:47:29,584 --> 01:47:32,748
They speak of democracy,

1995
01:47:32,789 --> 01:47:35,758
then support kings and dictators.

1996
01:47:35,792 --> 01:47:37,419
Changez...
(chuckles)

1997
01:47:40,697 --> 01:47:42,858
You have an office
in the faculty building.

1998
01:47:42,899 --> 01:47:43,888
Yes, I do.

1999
01:47:43,933 --> 01:47:45,093
Changez...

2000
01:47:48,237 --> 01:47:53,539
Many Muslims can
sympathize passively.

2001
01:47:53,576 --> 01:47:56,374
A mujahid acts.

2002
01:47:58,981 --> 01:48:01,449
There are items,

2003
01:48:01,484 --> 01:48:03,714
tools of resistance,

2004
01:48:03,753 --> 01:48:07,622
that we would like to store
in your office.

2005
01:48:10,160 --> 01:48:11,320
Yeah.

2006
01:48:13,097 --> 01:48:17,534
A wise and effective mujahid

2007
01:48:17,568 --> 01:48:21,402
appears to the enemy
as a negotiable man.

2008
01:48:22,439 --> 01:48:24,703
He hides behind masks.

2009
01:48:26,076 --> 01:48:28,340
Wear this mask for us, Changez.

2010
01:48:30,013 --> 01:48:33,005
I'm asking you
to join the fight.

2011
01:48:38,323 --> 01:48:40,985
I was his for the taking.

2012
01:48:41,025 --> 01:48:43,050
I had seen firsthand
the arrogant America

2013
01:48:43,094 --> 01:48:44,959
he described,

2014
01:48:44,996 --> 01:48:46,088
the blindness,

2015
01:48:46,131 --> 01:48:49,396
the hypocrisy, the xenophobia.

2016
01:48:49,434 --> 01:48:50,867
My anger had congealed,

2017
01:48:50,902 --> 01:48:53,769
hardened by injustice
and disappointment.

2018
01:48:53,805 --> 01:48:55,830
Of course I would fight.

2019
01:48:55,874 --> 01:48:58,468
Of course I would bleed the enemy.

2020
01:48:58,510 --> 01:49:01,479
But then he used that word...

2021
01:49:01,513 --> 01:49:03,640
Our only hope as a people

2022
01:49:03,681 --> 01:49:06,309
are the fundamental truths

2023
01:49:06,351 --> 01:49:08,183
given to us in the Q'uran.

2024
01:49:11,357 --> 01:49:15,987
We do that by focusing
on the fundamentals.

2025
01:49:18,664 --> 01:49:21,633
(solemn ethereal music)

2026
01:49:21,667 --> 01:49:25,865
♪

2027
01:49:25,905 --> 01:49:27,429
With due respect...

2028
01:49:31,577 --> 01:49:34,637
These young men were engaged
in their own valuation,

2029
01:49:34,680 --> 01:49:36,409
just like Underwood Samson,

2030
01:49:36,448 --> 01:49:40,408
moving human beings in and out
of binary columns:

2031
01:49:40,453 --> 01:49:44,514
worker, liability, American, Pakistani,

2032
01:49:44,558 --> 01:49:49,393
martyr, infidel, alive, dead.

2033
01:49:49,429 --> 01:49:52,398
I was tired of the reduction.

2034
01:49:52,432 --> 01:49:54,900
I was tired of deciding
from a distant perch

2035
01:49:54,935 --> 01:49:57,096
the fate of people
I did not know.

2036
01:49:59,206 --> 01:50:00,867
Yes, I'm a Pakistani.

2037
01:50:00,907 --> 01:50:02,306
Yes, I'm a Muslim.

2038
01:50:02,342 --> 01:50:05,311
Yes, I'm an opponent of
your country's assault on mine.

2039
01:50:05,345 --> 01:50:07,677
But that's not all I am.

2040
01:50:07,714 --> 01:50:09,773
We're both more
than these things, Bobby.

2041
01:50:11,485 --> 01:50:13,953
And I've never taken up arms,
and I never will,

2042
01:50:13,988 --> 01:50:17,719
so please, tell them
to leave my family alone.

2043
01:50:24,732 --> 01:50:26,927
(glass shatters, man shouts)

2044
01:50:26,968 --> 01:50:28,265
Hey!

2045
01:50:28,302 --> 01:50:29,360
Hand me those petrol bombs!

2046
01:50:29,403 --> 01:50:30,427
Wait a minute.

2047
01:50:30,471 --> 01:50:31,870
What's going on?

2048
01:50:31,906 --> 01:50:33,100
Where are you going?

2049
01:50:33,140 --> 01:50:35,233
Rainier's fate is not in my hands.

2050
01:50:35,276 --> 01:50:36,903
Stop all this!

2051
01:50:36,944 --> 01:50:38,070
Changez.

2052
01:50:38,112 --> 01:50:40,580
Hey, Changez!
Wait!

2053
01:50:40,615 --> 01:50:44,052
Police dogs!
Servants of America!

2054
01:50:44,086 --> 01:50:47,078
(people shouting)

2055
01:50:48,590 --> 01:50:50,182
(indistinct police radio transmission)

2056
01:50:52,628 --> 01:50:54,255
- Listen!
- I've said all I had to say.

2057
01:50:54,296 --> 01:50:56,423
I heard you back there.
I did.

2058
01:51:00,002 --> 01:51:02,800
I'm tired of taking sides too.

2059
01:51:02,838 --> 01:51:04,237
I just want to bring
my friend home.

2060
01:51:04,273 --> 01:51:05,900
When you picked a side
after 9/11,

2061
01:51:05,941 --> 01:51:07,135
you said they came to you.

2062
01:51:07,175 --> 01:51:08,904
So who invited you
to join the fight?

2063
01:51:08,944 --> 01:51:10,275
It was your friend, wasn't it?

2064
01:51:10,312 --> 01:51:12,542
Professor Rainier
was in Afghanistan in 2001.

2065
01:51:12,581 --> 01:51:14,242
I remember him talking about it.

2066
01:51:15,318 --> 01:51:16,376
Just tell me the truth!

2067
01:51:16,419 --> 01:51:17,681
You know the truth!

2068
01:51:17,720 --> 01:51:20,314
Rainier brought me in.
He was a case officer.

2069
01:51:22,091 --> 01:51:23,490
No, wait!
Wait, Changez.

2070
01:51:23,526 --> 01:51:25,255
Wait.

2071
01:51:25,295 --> 01:51:27,923
We can stop this right now,
you and me.

2072
01:51:27,964 --> 01:51:29,261
If that extraction team
comes in here,

2073
01:51:29,299 --> 01:51:31,267
all hell's gonna break loose,
and you know it.

2074
01:51:31,301 --> 01:51:32,734
Do you have any idea
what it means

2075
01:51:32,769 --> 01:51:35,533
for me to help the CIA
in my own country?

2076
01:51:35,571 --> 01:51:37,436
Please, Changez.

2077
01:51:37,473 --> 01:51:39,737
Try to see the man.

2078
01:51:39,776 --> 01:51:42,836
He has a wife... her name's Alissa...

2079
01:51:42,879 --> 01:51:44,972
and two small girls,
Sophie and Molly.

2080
01:51:45,014 --> 01:51:46,482
Let me call them, please.

2081
01:51:46,517 --> 01:51:49,111
Let me call them and tell them
that he's safe.

2082
01:51:49,153 --> 01:51:50,450
I can't.
I can't.

2083
01:51:50,487 --> 01:51:53,115
Sir, the cops are roughing up
the students.

2084
01:51:53,157 --> 01:51:54,454
Only you can control them!

2085
01:51:54,491 --> 01:51:55,822
I'll be right there.

2086
01:51:55,859 --> 01:51:57,656
I'm coming!

2087
01:51:57,695 --> 01:52:00,095
Then do it for your students,
for their future,

2088
01:52:00,130 --> 01:52:01,961
because you and I both agree
they deserve one.

2089
01:52:04,234 --> 01:52:07,203
(conflicted orchestral music)

2090
01:52:07,237 --> 01:52:12,331
♪

2091
01:52:20,051 --> 01:52:22,281
There's a butcher's shop
near Sheranwala Gate.

2092
01:52:22,320 --> 01:52:23,844
I've heard a student
talk about it.

2093
01:52:23,888 --> 01:52:25,685
There's a back room.

2094
01:52:25,724 --> 01:52:27,351
You can only get to it
through the freezer.

2095
01:52:27,392 --> 01:52:29,292
I heard Asal Mujahideen
sometimes use it.

2096
01:52:31,596 --> 01:52:32,756
Now call them off.

2097
01:52:34,799 --> 01:52:35,959
Thank you.

2098
01:52:39,371 --> 01:52:40,531
You did the right thing.

2099
01:52:44,342 --> 01:52:46,071
I'm calling it in.
Don't move.

2100
01:52:47,946 --> 01:52:50,780
(pounding at door)

2101
01:52:50,816 --> 01:52:52,977
Get out!
The police!

2102
01:52:55,187 --> 01:52:56,552
Stay calm!

2103
01:52:56,589 --> 01:52:58,318
No one go outside!

2104
01:52:58,357 --> 01:52:59,688
Junaid, calm them down.

2105
01:52:59,725 --> 01:53:01,488
Don't worry, sir.

2106
01:53:01,527 --> 01:53:04,087
Sameer, go outside.
Calm them.

2107
01:53:04,130 --> 01:53:05,358
Amreh, hello?

2108
01:53:05,398 --> 01:53:07,025
(distorted transmission)

2109
01:53:07,066 --> 01:53:09,694
Amreh, I know where Rainier is.

2110
01:53:09,735 --> 01:53:11,168
You're cutting out.

2111
01:53:11,203 --> 01:53:13,194
What?

2112
01:53:13,239 --> 01:53:14,297
Bobby, can you hear me?

2113
01:53:14,340 --> 01:53:15,830
At Sheranwala... hello?

2114
01:53:15,875 --> 01:53:16,864
Bobby, can you...

2115
01:53:16,909 --> 01:53:19,434
Police have been warned
and will assist.

2116
01:53:21,080 --> 01:53:23,743
At Sheran... hello?

2117
01:53:23,784 --> 01:53:25,115
Fuck.

2118
01:53:25,152 --> 01:53:27,848
Brothers, listen to me, please!

2119
01:53:31,491 --> 01:53:34,483
(people shouting in Urdu)

2120
01:53:36,930 --> 01:53:39,990
Everything's okay.
Sit down.

2121
01:53:40,033 --> 01:53:41,295
Did you call them off?

2122
01:53:41,334 --> 01:53:43,359
(phone trills)

2123
01:53:43,403 --> 01:53:46,372
(ominous music)

2124
01:53:46,406 --> 01:53:50,236
♪

2125
01:53:52,646 --> 01:53:55,616
(sound muffled and distorted)

2126
01:53:55,650 --> 01:54:01,401
♪

2127
01:54:11,032 --> 01:54:14,024
(people shouting)

2128
01:54:17,305 --> 01:54:19,273
Who were you texting?

2129
01:54:19,307 --> 01:54:20,740
My sister.

2130
01:54:20,775 --> 01:54:22,299
Show me your phone, Changez.

2131
01:54:22,343 --> 01:54:23,435
What?

2132
01:54:23,478 --> 01:54:24,707
Show me your phone.

2133
01:54:24,746 --> 01:54:25,906
Why?

2134
01:54:29,618 --> 01:54:32,178
Put your hands on the counter.

2135
01:54:32,221 --> 01:54:33,313
What are you doing?

2136
01:54:33,355 --> 01:54:34,447
He has a gun!
He has a gun!

2137
01:54:34,490 --> 01:54:36,321
What a fucker!

2138
01:54:36,358 --> 01:54:38,223
Move!

2139
01:54:38,260 --> 01:54:39,227
Get it?

2140
01:54:39,261 --> 01:54:40,319
