Yes, I did.

2147
01:55:01,651 --> 01:55:03,141
- Yeah?
- Yes.

2148
01:55:03,186 --> 01:55:04,619
Then what the fuck is this?

2149
01:55:07,857 --> 01:55:09,791
Why, Changez?

2150
01:55:09,826 --> 01:55:10,986
Why?

2151
01:55:13,963 --> 01:55:15,260
Kept us nice and busy

2152
01:55:15,298 --> 01:55:16,959
while you gave your pals
a head start, didn't you?

2153
01:55:17,000 --> 01:55:18,627
Huh?

2154
01:55:18,668 --> 01:55:20,932
You're making a mistake
that's gonna get us both killed.

2155
01:55:20,970 --> 01:55:22,130
Just give me your phone.

2156
01:55:24,240 --> 01:55:25,707
Get back!

2157
01:55:25,742 --> 01:55:27,733
(crowd murmuring)

2158
01:55:27,777 --> 01:55:28,938
(speaks Urdu)

2159
01:55:30,948 --> 01:55:33,416
Let's go, real slow.

2160
01:55:33,450 --> 01:55:36,613
Back!

2161
01:55:36,654 --> 01:55:37,850
Step back!

2162
01:55:39,082 --> 01:55:40,071
Step back!

2163
01:55:44,228 --> 01:55:46,890
Professor Khan is in danger!

2164
01:55:46,931 --> 01:55:49,923
(people shouting)

2165
01:55:51,202 --> 01:55:52,931
You're gonna get us
both killed, Bobby.

2166
01:55:55,406 --> 01:55:58,000
all: Professor! Professor!

2167
01:55:58,042 --> 01:55:59,202
(speaks Urdu)

2168
01:55:59,243 --> 01:56:02,509
(people shouting)

2169
01:56:02,547 --> 01:56:03,514
(gunshot)

2170
01:56:03,548 --> 01:56:04,537
Step back!

2171
01:56:05,750 --> 01:56:06,910
Step back!

2172
01:56:11,122 --> 01:56:12,646
We're with you, brother!

2173
01:56:12,691 --> 01:56:17,128
(people shouting)

2174
01:56:17,162 --> 01:56:18,993
Move!

2175
01:56:19,030 --> 01:56:19,997
(gunshot)

2176
01:56:20,031 --> 01:56:21,089
Ah!

2177
01:56:25,470 --> 01:56:26,382
Sameer!

2178
01:56:26,841 --> 01:56:27,788
Sameer!

2179
01:56:28,173 --> 01:56:30,937
(sound muffled and distorted)

2180
01:56:30,976 --> 01:56:32,308
(screams)

2181
01:56:32,345 --> 01:56:34,108
Step back!
Step back!

2182
01:56:34,146 --> 01:56:35,909
Just secure Bobby and
get the hell back here.

2183
01:56:35,948 --> 01:56:37,108
Go, go, go!

2184
01:56:38,584 --> 01:56:41,576
(screaming)

2185
01:56:44,724 --> 01:56:48,626
(people shouting)

2186
01:56:48,661 --> 01:56:49,650
(gunshot)

2187
01:56:49,695 --> 01:56:51,458
(screams)

2188
01:56:51,497 --> 01:56:55,934
(crowd chanting in Urdu)

2189
01:56:55,968 --> 01:56:58,198
(people shouting)

2190
01:56:58,237 --> 01:56:59,932
We got you, Bobby!

2191
01:56:59,972 --> 01:57:01,940
(screams)

2192
01:57:05,479 --> 01:57:07,379
Go, go, go, go, go, go!

2193
01:57:07,414 --> 01:57:10,406
(people shouting)

2194
01:57:12,452 --> 01:57:15,421
(crying)

2195
01:57:20,861 --> 01:57:23,830
(mournful music)

2196
01:57:23,864 --> 01:57:29,499
♪

2197
01:57:34,541 --> 01:57:35,668
Come on!

2198
01:57:38,179 --> 01:57:39,874
What the fuck happened?

2199
01:57:39,914 --> 01:57:41,381
He gave us away.

2200
01:57:41,416 --> 01:57:43,281
I caught him texting when
I went to get my phone.

2201
01:57:43,318 --> 01:57:44,751
That's why they killed Anse.

2202
01:57:44,786 --> 01:57:47,016
- When?
- Ah!

2203
01:57:47,055 --> 01:57:48,147
15 minutes ago.

2204
01:57:48,189 --> 01:57:50,054
- No, we found Rainier.
- I know. I know.

2205
01:57:50,091 --> 01:57:51,854
A butcher shop at Sheranwala Gate.

2206
01:57:51,893 --> 01:57:53,520
What are you talking about?

2207
01:57:53,561 --> 01:57:55,426
We found Rainier in a
morgue in Karachi.

2208
01:57:55,463 --> 01:57:57,158
We got word 20 minutes ago,

2209
01:57:57,198 --> 01:57:59,962
but he was dumped there
this morning.

2210
01:58:00,001 --> 01:58:02,993
This morning?
Shit.

2211
01:58:03,037 --> 01:58:05,938
Local intelligence verified
that Changez rejected Fazil.

2212
01:58:05,973 --> 01:58:07,134
We misread him.

2213
01:58:11,146 --> 01:58:13,171
(gasps)

2214
01:58:13,215 --> 01:58:14,307
Shit.

2215
01:58:16,385 --> 01:58:19,377
(crying)

2216
01:58:20,556 --> 01:58:23,525
(people shouting)

2217
01:58:27,029 --> 01:58:28,394
(bicycle bell chimes)

2218
01:58:30,332 --> 01:58:33,301
(rueful music)

2219
01:58:33,335 --> 01:58:38,376
♪

2220
01:59:01,898 --> 01:59:04,890
(chanting in Urdu)

2221
01:59:10,441 --> 01:59:14,810
Sameer's parents wish me
to address you.

2222
01:59:14,845 --> 01:59:19,145
They understand
our strong emotion.

2223
01:59:20,184 --> 01:59:22,846
Emotions give us courage.

2224
01:59:22,887 --> 01:59:25,879
(woman crying)

2225
01:59:27,691 --> 01:59:33,493
I have another message
from his family.

2226
01:59:33,531 --> 01:59:37,399
If our innocent, smiling Sameer
could hear it...

2227
01:59:41,706 --> 01:59:43,606
He would fully agree.

2228
01:59:45,377 --> 01:59:50,940
They ask us not to cry
for their son.

2229
01:59:50,982 --> 01:59:54,315
Too many tears have flowed
into the river.

2230
02:00:00,292 --> 02:00:04,922
They ask us not to take revenge
in their son's name.

2231
02:00:07,332 --> 02:00:10,096
Too much blood has
flowed into that river.

2232
02:00:14,440 --> 02:00:17,068
They ask us not to curse fate.

2233
02:00:18,411 --> 02:00:20,879
Allah holds our son
in His embrace.

2234
02:00:21,814 --> 02:00:24,783
(woman singing mournfully)

2235
02:00:24,817 --> 02:00:27,445
♪

2236
02:00:27,487 --> 02:00:30,479
(man chanting)

2237
02:00:33,559 --> 02:00:35,117
Wipe your tears!

2238
02:00:36,429 --> 02:00:40,092
And pray for a future

2239
02:00:40,132 --> 02:00:42,259
free of dictators and tyrants...

2240
02:00:43,402 --> 02:00:46,133
Free of all invaders.

2241
02:00:46,173 --> 02:00:49,870
Come, bring your loved ones.

2242
02:00:49,910 --> 02:00:55,542
Go tell the majestic sun
to preserve its precious rays.

2243
02:00:55,582 --> 02:00:59,678
We'll teach the core of our own
beings to glow with its light.

2244
02:01:19,040 --> 02:01:21,531
Would you please listen
to the whole story,

2245
02:01:21,576 --> 02:01:23,806
not just bits and pieces?

2246
02:01:23,845 --> 02:01:25,437
Do I have your word?

2247
02:01:25,480 --> 02:01:26,777
You do.

2248
02:01:26,814 --> 02:01:28,338
(clears throat)

2249
02:01:28,383 --> 02:01:29,873
Looks can be deceiving.

2250
02:01:32,620 --> 02:01:34,281
I am a lover of America.

2251
02:01:35,488 --> 02:01:38,457
(bright guitar music)

2252
02:01:38,491 --> 02:01:43,772
♪

